F4 "The 71342 is a high-speed 4K x 8 Dual-Port Static RAM containing a fully independent semaphore logic block to assist in arbitrating between ports. This block contains unassigned flags which can be accessed by either side, however, only one side can control the flag at any time. An automatic power down feature, controlled by CE and SEM, permits the on-chip circuitry of each port to enter a very low standby power mode (both CE and SEM HIGH)." 1950 300 50 H I L CNN "Description"
